author: @kentvesser9484
text: It really was a smart move on JYP's part to add Momo to the group late.  I think he realized that while the group was solid without her, the group was lacking an iconic main dancer and that has become increasingly important for a group to have.  Not only are they critical for the group's choreo, but they are critical for learning other groups' choreo for variety shows.  For girl groups especially having a main dancer who can also do not just the dances of the other girl groups as well as they do, but also do the dances of the boy groups well too is really important.  A really good random dance segment on Weekly Idol, Idol Room, Knowing Brothers, or other variety shows can really boost a group's image more than singing can usually, at least right after debut.
